How to update nodejs to the latest from https://nodejs.org/en/download
# Download and install nvm:
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.3/install.sh | bash

# in lieu of restarting the shell
\. "$HOME/.nvm/nvm.sh"

# Download and install Node.js:
nvm install 24

# Verify the Node.js version:
node -v # Should print "v24.12.0".

# Verify npm version:
npm -v # Should print "11.6.2".
Set the default version (optional):
If you want the newly installed version to be the default version used every time you open a new terminal, run:
bash
nvm alias default node
 
Managing Multiple Versions
The main advantage of NVM is its flexibility in managing multiple Node.js versions. 
List all available remote versions: nvm ls-remote
List installed versions: nvm ls
Switch to a different installed version: nvm use <version_number> (e.g., nvm use 20.9.0)
Uninstall a specific version: nvm uninstall <version_number>
